FuncDef:
The access-user user-queue recovery disable command disables automatic switchback from CAR to user queue.
The undo access-user user-queue recovery disable command enables automatic switchback from CAR to user queue.
By default, automatic switchback from CAR to user queue is enabled.
ExtraInfo:
Usage Scenario
Switchback from CAR to user queue is enabled by default. To disable automatic switchback from CAR to user queue, run the access-user user-queue recovery disable command.
Precautions
L2TP users on the LNS side do not support automatic switchback from CAR to user queue.
